node.text:
We are excited to introduce our Brewing for Diversity Scholarship initiative in partnership with @ucsdextension and their brewing program! Ballast Point will grant one scholarship per year, and recipients will be selected by partner team members and the @sdbrewers Guild Inclusion Committee. We can’t wait to support YOU and a more inclusive brewing community. 

Visit the link in our bio for more information on how to apply!

node.text:
Imagine that your artistic vision was so inspiring that it warranted a Hot Wheels replica! Well, that’s exactly what happened to a local San Diego businessman 🔥

This week we had the chance to sit down with the Co-founder of @sdwrap, Ramin Niroomand. Ramin’s team of experts and passionate enthusiasts help create dream cars by wrapping their customers’ luxury vehicles. Ramin talks about how passion and persistence keep him artistically motivated to break barriers and try new things. 

Link in bio to listen 😎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ballast Point Brewing Co. in San Diego, California with @caffecalabria, @ballastpointlongbeach, @ballastpointanaheim, @ballastpointsandiego, and @homebrewmart.

node.text:
In honor of National Beer Lover's Day, we are celebrating the triumphant return of Victory At Sea 🍻🌊

This Imperial Porter is a bold, smooth brew with just the right amount of sweetness. We infused this robust porter with vanilla and San Diego’s own @caffecalabria coffee beans ☕️

The subtle roasted notes and minimal acidity of the cold-brewed coffee balances perfectly with the sweet caramel undertones of the malt, creating a winning combination for your palate.

Victory at Sea is available in 16 oz. 4-packs at all of our tasting rooms. They're the perfect way to kick off fall 👏🏼

Looking to make it even better? Pick up a Sculpin, Grapefruit Sculpin, or Swingin Friar Ale in our new 16oz cans. Because tbh those 4oz make a difference, and you deserve it.
